==Romanian==
===Etymology===
Either a substratum word (compare Albanian ''[[ylber]]''), or a compound of *''curcu'' from Latin ''[[circus]]'' and an uncertain *''beu'', compare Italian ''[[arcobaleno]]'' and Sardinian (Logudorese) ''arcubaradu''. 

[[Category:Romance etymology]]
see: www.geocities.com/protoillyrian for more information

